#   DIFF-007: `diff:<largefile>` silently EMPTY ‚Äî `WEAVEEmitFull` outtoks overflow

`be diff:<file>` on a large file produces NO output and exits 0. Root cause:
`WEAVEEmitFull` carves a fixed 65536-token buffer and accumulates the UNION of
base+wt weave tokens into one hunk; when that union exceeds 65536 the `u32bFeed1`
returns NOROOM, which is swallowed (`ret=fo; goto cleanup`) ‚Üí zero hunks emitted,
exit 0. Real bug. Split from [[DIFF-005]]'s bare-diff re-investigation. Method:
[Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  Reproduced in `$HOME/todo/PTR-005`. `be diff:sniff/GET.c` (and `PATCH.c`,
    `POST.c`) ‚Üí EMPTY; smaller files render fine.
 -  Measured threshold over all 17 changed files: EMPTY exactly when wt-tokens are
    large ‚Äî GET.c (35471), PATCH.c (31786), POST.c (48653) ‚Üí ALL EMPTY; largest
    WORKING = SNIFF.exe.c (20170), then SUBS.c (19266), PUT.c (18602), AT.c (16511).
    Boundary sits between wt‚âà20K (works) and wt‚âà32K (empty) ‚Äî matches the base‚à™wt
    UNION hitting the 65536 cap.
 -  Code: `WEAVEEmitFull` carves `a_carve(u32, outtoks, 1UL << 16)` = 65536
    (`graf/WEAVE.c:1030`) and accumulates the union of base+wt tokens into ONE hunk;
    the only flush (`WEAVE.c:1092`) is BYTE-based at `WEAVE_FULL_HUNK_MAX` (1 MB),
    which a ~95 KB file never reaches. Once token count > 65536, `u32bFeed1(outtoks,‚Ä¶)`
    returns NOROOM ‚Üí `ret=fo; goto cleanup` (`WEAVE.c:1099-1101`) ‚Üí no hunk, empty
    output, NOROOM swallowed to exit 0.
 -  Same files render fine in BARE `be diff:` because `WEAVEEmitDiff` flushes each
    small hunk separately and never accumulates the whole file.
 -  Red herring: `./build-debug/bin/be` (relative argv[0]) makes the sub-recursion's
    `execvp` fail after `chdir` into the sniff mount (`beagle/SUBS.c:331`); absolute-path
    invocation removes that message but the diff is STILL empty ‚Äî the overflow is the
    real cause.

### Goals
 -  `be diff:<largefile>` renders its full-file diff (or a bounded one) instead of
    silently emitting nothing; the NOROOM is never swallowed into a success exit.

### Constraints
 -  graf/WEAVE change gates for review. Add a large-file (>65536-token) diff test that
    asserts non-empty output.

##  WIP

### Design decisions
 -  Two complementary fixes: (1) flush `WEAVEEmitFull` by TOKEN-count too (not only the
    1 MB byte cap) so the buffer never overflows; (2) stop swallowing NOROOM ‚Äî propagate
    it so a truncated/failed diff is an error, not a silent exit 0.
 -  Note: [[DIFF-005]] option-a (bound large files ‚Üí `WEAVEEmitDiff`) would INCIDENTALLY
    make GET.c/PATCH.c/POST.c render, masking this ‚Äî but the swallowed-NOROOM and missing
    token-flush should be fixed regardless.

